Corporation Act.
4.
The aggregate number of shares of capital stock which the Corporation shall have the
authority to issue is nine thousand nine hundred (9,900), of which 100 shares shall be known
as Class A Common Stock with a par value of one cent ($.01) per share, and nine thousand
eight hundred (9,800) shares shall be known as Class B Common Stock with a par value of
one cent ($.01) per share. The preferences, limitations, and relative rights of the Class A
and Class B Common Stock shall be identical except (unless and to the extent otherwise
made mandatory by law) the holders of Class B Common Stock shall have no right to vote
for the election of directors or for any other purpose or consent in leu thereof and shall not
be entitled to receive notice of any meeting of shareholders and all voting rights shall be
vested entirely in the holders of Class A Common Stock. The Corporation, subject to
Articles 2.38 and 4 08 of the Texas Business Corporation Act, as amended, may purchase
directly or indirectly, its own shares to the extent of the aggregate and unrestricted Capital or
reduction surplus available therefor.
5
The Corporation will not commence business or incur indebtedness, except such as
shall be incidental to its organization or to obtaining subscriptions to or payment for its
shares, until it has received consideration for the issuance of shares in the amount of at least
one thousand dollars, consisting of money, labor done, or property actually received.
The number of directors constituting the initial board of directors of the Corporation
is three, and the names and addresses of the persons who are to serve as the directors until
the first annual meeting of the shareholders and until their successors are elected and shall
qualify are as follows:
